<p>The <b>hectare</b> (<span class=3D"rt-commentedText nowrap"><span class=
=3D"IPA nopopups noexcerpt" lang=3D"en-fonipa"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Help:IPA/English" title=3D"Help:IPA/English">/<span style=3D"b=
order-bottom:1px dotted"><span title=3D"/=CB=88/: primary stress follows">=
=CB=88</span><span title=3D"'h' in 'hi'">h</span><span title=3D"/=C9=9B/: '=
e' in 'dress'">=C9=9B</span><span title=3D"'k' in 'kind'">k</span><span tit=
le=3D"'t' in 'tie'">t</span><span title=3D"/=C9=9B=C9=99r/: 'are' in 'bare'=
">=C9=9B=C9=99r</span></span>,<span class=3D"wrap"> </span>-<span style=3D"=
border-bottom:1px dotted"><span title=3D"'t' in 'tie'">t</span><span title=
=3D"/=C9=91=CB=90r/: 'ar' in 'far'">=C9=91=CB=90r</span></span>/</a></span>=
</span>; <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SI" class=3D"mw-redirect"=
 title=3D"SI">SI</a> symbol: <b>ha</b>) is a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Non-SI_units_mentioned_in_the_SI" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D=
"Non-SI units mentioned in the SI">non-SI</a> <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Metric_unit" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Metric unit">metric=
 unit</a> of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Area" title=3D"Area">=
area</a> equal to a square with 100-<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Metre" title=3D"Metre">metre</a> sides (1&nbsp;hm<sup>2</sup>), that is, =
10,000 square metres (10,000 m<sup>2</sup>), and is primarily used in the m=
easurement of land. There are 100 hectares in one square kilometre. An <a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Acre" title=3D"Acre">acre</a> is about=
 0.405 hectares and thus one hectare is about 2.47 acres.
</p>
