<p>The hectare (<span class=3D"rt-commentedText nowrap"><span class=3D"IPA =
nopopups noexcerpt" lang=3D"en-fonipa"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Help:IPA/English" title=3D"Help:IPA/English">/<span style=3D"border-bo=
ttom:1px dotted"><span title=3D"/=CB=88/: primary stress follows">=CB=88</s=
pan><span title=3D"'h' in 'hi'">h</span><span title=3D"/=C9=9B/: 'e' in 'dr=
ess'">=C9=9B</span><span title=3D"'k' in 'kind'">k</span><span title=3D"'t'=
 in 'tie'">t</span><span title=3D"/=C9=9B=C9=99r/: 'are' in 'bare'">=C9=9B=
=C9=99r</span></span>,<span class=3D"wrap"> </span>-<span style=3D"border-b=
ottom:1px dotted"><span title=3D"'t' in 'tie'">t</span><span title=3D"/=C9=
=91=CB=90/: 'a' in 'father'">=C9=91=CB=90</span><span title=3D"'r' in 'rye'=
">r</span></span>/</a></span></span><sup id=3D"cite_ref-2" class=3D"referen=
ce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hectare#cite_note-2"><span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>2<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup=
>), although not a unit of SI, is the only named unit of area that is <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-SI_units_mentioned_in_the_SI#Units_=
officially_accepted_for_use_with_the_SI" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Non=
-SI units mentioned in the SI">accepted for use with SI units</a>.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-BIPM2006Ch5_3-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Hectare#cite_note-BIPM2006Ch5-3"><span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">[</span>3<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The name was co=
ined in French, from the Latin <span title=3D"Latin-language text"><i lang=
=3D"la">=C4=81rea</i></span>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-4" class=3D"reference"><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hectare#cite_note-4"><span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> In pr=
actice the hectare is fully derived from the SI, being equivalent to a squa=
re hectometre. It is widely used throughout the world for the measurement o=
f large areas of land,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-sibrochuretable6_5-0" class=3D"re=
ference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hectare#cite_note-sibroch=
uretable6-5"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">]</span></a></sup> and it is the legal unit of measure in domains conc=
erned with land ownership, planning, and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Land_management" title=3D"Land management">management</a>, including=
 law (<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deed" title=3D"Deed">land de=
eds</a>), agriculture, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Forestry" t=
itle=3D"Forestry">forestry</a>, and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Town_planning" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Town planning">town plannin=
g</a> throughout the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/European_Unio=
n" title=3D"European Union">European Union</a>,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-6" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hectare#cite_note-6=
"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>6<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</spa=
n></a></sup> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Africa" title=
=3D"South Africa">South Africa</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/New_Zealand" title=3D"New Zealand">New Zealand</a>, <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australia" title=3D"Australia">Australia</a>, Canada an=
d the United Kingdom.
However, the United States and Myanmar (Burma)<sup id=3D"cite_ref-World_Fac=
tbook_7-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hec=
tare#cite_note-World_Factbook-7"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>7<spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-8" class=3D"=
reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hectare#cite_note-8"><s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>8<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></=
a></sup> use the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Acre" title=3D"Ac=
re">acre</a> instead of the hectare for measuring surface or land area.
</p><p>In many countries, metrification redefined or clarified existing mea=
sures in terms of metric units. The following legacy units of area have bee=
n redefined as being equal to one hectare:<sup id=3D"cite_ref-9" class=3D"r=
eference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hectare#cite_note-9"><sp=
an class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>9<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a=
></sup>
</p>
<ul><li><i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jerib" title=3D"Jerib">=
Jerib</a></i> (<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Persian_language" t=
itle=3D"Persian language">Persian</a>: <span lang=3D"fa" dir=3D"rtl">=D8=AC=
=D8=B1=DB=8C=D8=A8</span>) in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran=
" title=3D"Iran">Iran</a></li>
<li><i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jerib" title=3D"Jerib">Djer=
ib</a></i> (<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkish_language" titl=
e=3D"Turkish language">Turkish</a>: <i lang=3D"tr">cerip</i>) in <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkey" title=3D"Turkey">Turkey</a><sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-Chisholm1911_10-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Hectare#cite_note-Chisholm1911-10"><span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">[</span>10<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup></li>
<li><i>Gongqing</i> (<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Traditional_C=
hinese_characters" title=3D"Traditional Chinese characters">traditional Chi=
nese</a>: <span lang=3D"zh-Hant">=E5=85=AC=E9=A0=83</span>; <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Simplified_Chinese_characters" title=3D"Simplifie=
d Chinese characters">simplified Chinese</a>: <span lang=3D"zh-Hans">=E5=85=
=AC=E9=A1=B7</span>; <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pinyin" title=
=3D"Pinyin">pinyin</a>: <i><span lang=3D"zh-Latn">g=C5=8Dngq=C7=90ng</span>=
</i>) in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China" title=3D"China">Ch=
ina</a></li>
<li><i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Manzana_(unit)" title=3D"Ma=
nzana (unit)">Manzana</a></i> in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A=
rgentina" title=3D"Argentina">Argentina</a></li>
<li><i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bunder" title=3D"Bunder">Bu=
nder</a></i> in the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Netherlands" t=
itle=3D"Netherlands">Netherlands</a> (until 1937)<sup id=3D"cite_ref-11" cl=
ass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hectare#cite_not=
e-11"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>11<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]=
</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-12" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hectare#cite_note-12"><span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">[</span>12<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup></li></ul>
<p>In Mexico, land area measurements are commonly given as combinations of =
hectares, ares, and centiares.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-13" class=3D"reference"><=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hectare#cite_note-13"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>13<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>=
 These are commonly written separated by a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Hyphen" title=3D"Hyphen">hyphen</a>; for example, <i>1-21-00.26 ha=
</i> would mean 1 hectare, 21 are, and 0.26 centiare (<span class=3D"nowrap=
"><span data-sort-value=3D"7004121002600000000=E2=99=A0"></span>12<span sty=
le=3D"margin-left:.25em;">100</span>.26&nbsp;m<sup>2</sup></span>).
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"History">History</h2><span =
class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DHectare&amp;action=3De=
dit&amp;section=3D2" title=3D"Edit section: History"><span>edit</span></a><=
span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The metric system of measurement was first given a legal basis in 1795 b=
y the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/French_Revolution" title=3D"=
French Revolution">French Revolutionary</a> government.  The law of <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/French_Republican_Calendar" class=3D"mw-r=
edirect" title=3D"French Republican Calendar">18 Germinal, Year III</a> (7 =
April 1795) defined five units of measure:<sup id=3D"cite_ref-14" class=3D"=
reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hectare#cite_note-14"><=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>14<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span>=
</a></sup>
</p>
<ul><li>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metre" title=3D"Metre"=
>metre</a> for length</li>
<li>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hectare#Are">are</a> (100&=
nbsp;m<sup>2</sup>) for area [of land]</li>
<li>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/St%C3%A8re" class=3D"mw-re=
direct" title=3D"St=C3=A8re">st=C3=A8re</a> (1&nbsp;m<sup>3</sup>) for volu=
me of stacked firewood<sup id=3D"cite_ref-15" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hectare#cite_note-15"><span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">[</span>15<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup></li>
<li>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Litre" title=3D"Litre">lit=
re</a> (1&nbsp;dm<sup>3</sup>) for volumes of liquid</li>
<li>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gram" title=3D"Gram">gram<=
/a> for mass</li></ul>
<p>In 1960, when the metric system was updated as the International System =
of Units (SI), the <i>are</i> did not receive international recognition.  T=
he <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Committee_for_Wei=
ghts_and_Measures" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"International Committee f=
or Weights and Measures">International Committee for Weights and Measures</=
a> (<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyl=
es:r1038841319"><span class=3D"rt-commentedText tooltip tooltip-dotted" tit=
le=3D"in French: Comit=C3=A9 international des poids et mesures">CIPM</span=
>) makes no mention of the <i>are</i> in the 2019 edition of the SI brochur=
e, but classifies the hectare as a "Non-SI unit accepted for use with the I=
nternational System of Units".<sup id=3D"cite_ref-16" class=3D"reference"><=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hectare#cite_note-16"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>16<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In 1972, the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/European_Econo=
mic_Community" title=3D"European Economic Community">European Economic Comm=
unity</a> (EEC) passed directive 71/354/EEC,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-17" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hectare#cite_note-1=
7"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>17<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</s=
pan></a></sup> which catalogued the units of measure that might be used wit=
hin the Community.  The units that were catalogued replicated the recommend=
ations of the CGPM, supplemented by a few other units including the <i>are<=
/i> (and implicitly the <i>hectare</i>) whose use was limited to the measur=
ement of land.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Unit_family">Unit family</h=
2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</=
span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DHectare&amp;ac=
tion=3Dedit&amp;section=3D3" title=3D"Edit section: Unit family"><span>edit=
</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size mw-halign-right" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb">=
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Hectare_Diagram.svg" class=3D=
"mw-file-description"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/co=
mmons/thumb/8/80/Hectare_Diagram.svg/500px-Hectare_Diagram.svg.png" decodin=
g=3D"async" width=3D"340" height=3D"388" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-fil=
e-width=3D"456" data-file-height=3D"520"></a><figcaption> Definition of a <=
i>hectare</i> and of an <i>are</i></figcaption></figure>
<p>The names <i>centiare</i>, <i>deciare</i>, <i>decare</i> and <i>hectare<=
/i> are derived by adding the standard <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Metric_prefix" title=3D"Metric prefix">metric prefixes</a> to the orig=
inal base unit of area, the <i>are</i>.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Decimilliare">Decimilliare<=
/h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[=
</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DHectare&amp;=
action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D4" title=3D"Edit section: Decimilliare"><span>e=
dit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The <b>decimilliare</b> (dma, sometimes seen in <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Cadastre" title=3D"Cadastre">cadastre</a> area evaluation =
of real estate plots) is <link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D=
"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1214402035"><span class=3D"sfrac">=E2=81=A0<span c=
lass=3D"tion"><span class=3D"num">1</span><span class=3D"sr-only">/</span><=
span class=3D"den">10,000</span></span>=E2=81=A0</span> are or one square d=
ecimetre.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-18" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Hectare#cite_note-18"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</sp=
an>18<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>  Such usage of a <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metric_prefix#Double_prefixes" title=3D=
"Metric prefix">double prefix</a> is non-standard. The decimilliare is (100=
&nbsp;mm)<sup>2</sup> or roughly a four-inch-by-four-inch square. (The deci=
milliare is smaller by approximately 3.1%.)
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Centiare">Centiare</h3><spa=
n class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DHectare&amp;action=
=3Dedit&amp;section=3D5" title=3D"Edit section: Centiare"><span>edit</span>=
</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The <b>centiare</b> is one square metre.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-19" class=3D=
"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hectare#cite_note-19">=
<span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>19<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span=
></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-20" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hectare#cite_note-20"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</=
span>20<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Deciare">Deciare</h3><span =
class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DHectare&amp;action=3De=
dit&amp;section=3D6" title=3D"Edit section: Deciare"><span>edit</span></a><=
span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The <b>deciare</b> (rarely used) is ten square metres.<sup id=3D"cite_re=
f-21" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hectare#=
cite_note-21"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>21<span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Are">Are</h3><span class=3D=
"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DHectare&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;=
section=3D7" title=3D"Edit section: Are"><span>edit</span></a><span class=
=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">"Are (unit)"=
 redirects here. For the English verb, see <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/To_be_(disambiguation)" class=3D"mw-redirect mw-disambig" title=3D=
"To be (disambiguation)">To Be</a>.</div>
<p>The <b>are</b> (<span class=3D"rt-commentedText nowrap"><span class=3D"I=
PA nopopups noexcerpt" lang=3D"en-fonipa"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Help:IPA/English" title=3D"Help:IPA/English">/<span style=3D"border=
-bottom:1px dotted"><span title=3D"/=C9=91=CB=90r/: 'ar' in 'far'">=C9=91=
=CB=90r</span></span>/</a></span></span><sup id=3D"cite_ref-22" class=3D"re=
ference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hectare#cite_note-22"><sp=
an class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>22<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></=
a></sup> or <span class=3D"rt-commentedText nowrap"><span class=3D"IPA nopo=
pups noexcerpt" lang=3D"en-fonipa"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Help:IPA/English" title=3D"Help:IPA/English">/<span style=3D"border-bottom=
:1px dotted"><span title=3D"/=C9=9B=C9=99r/: 'are' in 'bare'">=C9=9B=C9=99r=
</span></span>/</a></span></span><sup id=3D"cite_ref-23" class=3D"reference=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hectare#cite_note-23"><span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>23<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup=
>) is a unit of area, equal to 100 square metres (<span class=3D"nowrap"><s=
pan data-sort-value=3D"7001100000000000000=E2=99=A0"></span>10&nbsp;m =C3=
=97 10&nbsp;m</span>), used for measuring land area. It was defined by olde=
r forms of the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metric_system" titl=
e=3D"Metric system">metric system</a>, but is now outside the modern <a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_System_of_Units" title=3D"=
International System of Units">International System of Units</a> (SI).<sup =
id=3D"cite_ref-24" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Hectare#cite_note-24"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>24<span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> It is still commonly used in speech =
to measure real estate, in particular in Indonesia, India, and in various E=
uropean countries.
</p><p>In <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russian_language" title=
=3D"Russian language">Russian</a> and some other languages of the former <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soviet_Union" title=3D"Soviet Union"=
>Soviet Union</a>, the <i>are</i> is called <span title=3D"Russian-language=
 text"><i lang=3D"ru-Latn">sotka</i></span> (<a href=3D"https://ru.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/%D0%90%D1%80" class=3D"extiw" title=3D"ru:=D0=90=D1=80">=D1=81=
=D0=BE=D1=82=D0=BA=D0=B0</a>: 'a&nbsp;hundred', i.e. 100&nbsp;m<sup>2</sup>=
 or <link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyl=
es:r1214402035"><span class=3D"sfrac">=E2=81=A0<span class=3D"tion"><span c=
lass=3D"num">1</span><span class=3D"sr-only">/</span><span class=3D"den">10=
0</span></span>=E2=81=A0</span> hectare). It is used to describe the size o=
f suburban <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dacha" title=3D"Dacha">=
dacha</a> or <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allotment_garden" cla=
ss=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Allotment garden">allotment garden</a> plots or=
 small city parks where the hectare would be too large. Many Russian dachas=
 are 6 ares in size (in Russian, <span title=3D"Russian-language text"><spa=
n lang=3D"ru">=D1=88=D0=B5=D1=81=D1=82=D1=8C =D1=81=D0=BE=D1=82=D0=BE=D0=BA=
</span></span>).
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Decare">Decare</h3><span cl=
ass=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DHectare&amp;action=3Dedi=
t&amp;section=3D8" title=3D"Edit section: Decare"><span>edit</span></a><spa=
n class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The <b>decare</b> or <b>dekare</b> (<span class=3D"rt-commentedText nowr=
ap"><span class=3D"IPA nopopups noexcerpt" lang=3D"en-fonipa"><a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA/English" title=3D"Help:IPA/English">/<=
span style=3D"border-bottom:1px dotted"><span title=3D"/=CB=88/: primary st=
ress follows">=CB=88</span><span title=3D"'d' in 'dye'">d</span><span title=
=3D"/=C9=9B/: 'e' in 'dress'">=C9=9B</span><span title=3D"'k' in 'kind'">k<=
/span><span title=3D"/=C9=91=CB=90r/: 'ar' in 'far'">=C9=91=CB=90r</span></=
span>,<span class=3D"wrap"> </span>-<span style=3D"border-bottom:1px dotted=
"><span title=3D"/=C9=9B=C9=99r/: 'are' in 'bare'">=C9=9B=C9=99r</span></sp=
an>/</a></span></span>) is derived from <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Deca-" title=3D"Deca-">deca</a></i> and <i>are</i>, and is equal t=
o 10 ares or 1000 square metres.  It is used in <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Norway" title=3D"Norway">Norway</a><sup id=3D"cite_ref-25" cl=
ass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hectare#cite_not=
e-25"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>25<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]=
</span></a></sup> and in the former <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Ottoman_Empire" title=3D"Ottoman Empire">Ottoman</a> areas of the <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Middle_East" title=3D"Middle East">Middle=
 East</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bulgaria" title=3D"B=
ulgaria">Bulgaria</a><sup id=3D"cite_ref-26" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hectare#cite_note-26"><span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">[</span>26<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> as a measu=
re of land area.  The names of the older land measures of similar size are =
usually used, redefined as exactly one decare:
</p>
<ul><li><span title=3D"Greek-language text"><i lang=3D"el-Latn"><a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stremma" title=3D"Stremma">Stremma</a></i></s=
pan> in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Greece" title=3D"Greece">G=
reece</a><sup id=3D"cite_ref-27" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Hectare#cite_note-27"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</sp=
an>27<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup></li>
<li><span title=3D"Turkish-language text"><i lang=3D"tr"><a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dunam" title=3D"Dunam">Dunam</a>, dunum, dulum, donu=
m, or d=C3=B6n=C3=BCm</i></span> in the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Balkans" title=3D"Balkans">Balkans</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Israel" title=3D"Israel">Israel</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Palestine" title=3D"Palestine">Palestine</a>, <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jordan" title=3D"Jordan">Jordan</a>, <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lebanon" title=3D"Lebanon">Lebanon</a>, <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syria" title=3D"Syria">Syria</a>, and <=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkey" title=3D"Turkey">Turkey</a>=
<sup id=3D"cite_ref-28" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Hectare#cite_note-28"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>28<spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup></li>
<li><span title=3D"Norwegian-language text"><i lang=3D"no"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Norwegian_units_of_measurement#Area" title=3D"Norw=
egian units of measurement">M=C3=A5l</a></i></span> in Norway.</li></ul>
